{
  "stem": "1799.3",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 621.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And there was what they called appell, which was a call to gather in usually a large, flat courtyard or court area.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they would call names.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And, and they would say, gather your-- order us around to go and march to, to work.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There was a certain formality in this appell, which means a call to order, which happened daily.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, my clothing at that time, they were mostly rags that were tied together, depending on the time of the year.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "If it was wintertime, there were more rags.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it wasn't until we got to Auschwitz that we actually got a uniform-- you know, the blue and white striped uniform.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But in these camps, pre-Auschwitz and after Auschwitz, we just wore whatever we could manage to, to put together to protect our bodies.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Did not even all have shoes.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Sometimes we had rags wrapped around our feet.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I had that at one time, but I was able to, I think, usually have some kind of shoe on me.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Maybe not matching, but shoes.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And very often not enough clothing or rags to keep the body warm, so that we had to duck for cover at times, or we, we tried to acquire more rags to cover our bodies.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Right.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was in a number--",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, there in Graditz I was in the beginning of '43.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then for about a year and a half, I was in a series of camps in the Sudeten area of Czechoslovakia, which were the mountainous-- the mountainous region between Germany and Czechoslovakia, which had a lot of forced labor camps.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But I don't-- in my mind, I don't remember every single one of them, until I got to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
